  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "When trying to simulate an event on an element in a portal, the event never fires with Simulate, but it does with the browser's dispatchEvent:\n\n```\nvar MyComponent = React.createClass({\n  handleMouseDown: function() {\n    console.log('mouse down pushed!');\n  },\n\n  render: function() {\n    return (\n      <Portal> \n        <div ref='myDiv' onMouseDown={this.handleMouseDown} />\n      </Portal>\n    );\n  }\n});\n\nrendered = reactTestUtils.renderIntoDocument(<MyComponent />);\n\nvar myDiv = rendered.refs.myDiv;\nreactTestUtils.Simulate.mouseDown(myDiv);\n\nvar downEvent = document.createEvent('MouseEvents');\ndownEvent.initEvent('mousedown', true, true);\nmyDiv.dispatchEvent(downEvent); // 'mouse down pushed!'\n```\n",
